CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 30, 1960, pg. A2 reads: "At Frog Symposium - The above group got together for a chat following the Frogs' symposium on Sunday in chapel on the campus of Chatham College. Left to right Boyd L. Wilson, J. Craig Kuhn, member of the City Council, who repreesnted [sic] mayor Joseph Barr; Lester B. Granger, executive director, National Urban League, guest speaker for the event; Roland Sawyer, who presided at the symposium, and Louis Mason Jr., who commented on the progress of Negroes in Allegheny County.  Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of FROGS members, from left: Boyd L. Wilson, J. Craig Kuhn, Lester B. Granger, Roland Sawyer, and Louis Mason Jr., standing in Chatham College chapel for FROGS symposium
